{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "SB51", "title": "Permanent standard time.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Permanentstandardtime"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing state law, Proposition 7, an initiative measure approved by the voters at the November 6, 2018, statewide general election, sets the standard time for California and sets daylight saving time to begin each March and end each November, as specified. Proposition 7 authorizes the Legislature to amend these provisions by a 23 vote to change the dates and times of the daylight saving time period, consistent with federal law, and authorizes the Legislature to amend these provisions by a 23 vote to provide for the application of year-round daylight saving time when authorized by federal law.\n\nThis bill would repeal daylight saving time in the state and the provisions regarding the Legislature's authority to amend the above-described provisions by a 23 vote. The bill would instead require the state and all political subdivisions of the state to observe year-round standard time. The bill would exempt the state and all political subdivisions of the state from the provisions of federal law that establish the advancement of time. The bill would make related findings and declarations."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. To Com. on RLS. for assignment. To print.", "date": "2024-12-18", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["introduction"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be acted upon on or after January 18.", "date": "2024-12-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Read first time.", "date": "2025-01-06", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities"